    • Constructor Detail

      • Geometry

        public Geometry(int numVertices,
        int numIndices,
        boolean usesColors,
        boolean usesTexturesUV)
        Creates a new Geometry.
        Parameters:
        numVertices - Number of vertices.
        numIndices - Number of indices (the indices are used to render the vertices in the specified order).
        usesColors - true if the geometry stores colors, false otherwise.
        usesTexturesUV - true if the geometry stores texture coordinates, false otherwise.

        public void addColor(Color color)

        Parameters:
        color - Color.

      • getColor

        public Color getColor(int index)
        Returns the Color located at the specified index of the array of colors.
        Parameters:
        index - Index.
        Returns:
        Color or null if this Geometry does not contain color information.

      • getNumColors

        public int getNumColors()
        Returns the number of colors of this Geometry. If this Geometry uses colors, there should be one color per defined vertex.
        Returns:
        Number of colors, or -1 if this Geometry does not use colors.

      • addTextureUV

        public void addTextureUV(Vector2 textureUV)
        Adds a pair of texture UV coordinates to this Geometry. The pair of texture UV coordinates will be associated to the vertex position located at the same index.
        Parameters:
        textureUV - Texture UV coordinates.

      • getTextureUV

        public Vector2 getTextureUV(int index)
        Returns the texture UV coordinates located at the specified index of the array of texture UV coordinates.
        Parameters:
        index - Index.
        Returns:
        Texture UV coordinates or null if this Geometry does not contain texture information.

      • getNumTexturesUV

        public int getNumTexturesUV()
        Returns the number of texture UV coordinates of this Geometry. If this Geometry uses texture UV coordinates, there should be one texture UV coordinate pair per defined vertex.
        Returns:
        Number of texture UV coordinates, or -1 if this Geometry does not use texture UV coordinates.
